raw_response:
When served, **Honey Cake**—including the Tunisian Jewish Djerban version adapted to be vegan with silan (date syrup)—appears as a **solid, loaf-shaped cake with a moist, dense yet tender crumb**. It is typically baked in a loaf or round pan, resulting in a shape similar to a traditional pound cake or bundt cake, sliced into portions for serving[1][3].

**Visual appearance:**  
- The cake has a **rich, golden to deep amber color**, enhanced by the dark silan or honey used.
